## Code of Conduct
1. Please be kind to one another, remember the human.
2. Spam and unsolicited advertisements are not permitted.
3. Trolling, flaming, baiting or other attention-stealing behaviour is not allowed.
4. Discrimination or otherwise demeaning a group of people is not permitted, this is an inclusive space and we ask that you respect this.

These rules only apply to this Revolt server and any public communication with the team, such as GitHub discussions or issues. Communities may apply these rules to their own servers.

## Chat Rules
1. Zero tolerance on adult content / discussion.
2. This server is intended to stay on-topic surrounding Revolt, please refer to channel descriptions where necessary.
3. Politics discussion / religious debates are not allowed on this server. (exceptions may be made if there is an impact on Revolt, e.g. chat control, online safety act; this is at moderator's discretion)
4. Avoid repeatedly pinging users to get their attention, once is enough.
5. Revolt does not endorse other instances and is not responsible for anything you may see on them as such please do not share them here (if you need help, please use [revoltchat/self-hosted issues](<https://github.com/revoltchat/self-hosted>)).
6. Stick to English-only where possible (i.e. casual conversations should be in English, but <#01FY1ENB2K17625XAB985HVWSQ> requests may be more effectively handled in another language), we can't moderate other languages effectively.
7. Keep personal drama and moderation issues out of this chat, if you have a problem with someone, sort it out in private / report in-app / send us an email at contact@revolt.chat
8. Please keep complaints about other platforms minimal, this isn't the place for it.

### Mod Mail: [lounge@revolt.chat](mailto:lounge@revolt.chat) (reports + appeals)
